  {
    "id": "2079469815975018964",
    "text": "Another tanker was attacked in the Strait of Hormuz as renewed hostilities empty the waterway, while a threat by Houthi rebels to blockade Saudi Arabia in the Red Sea heightened regional maritime risks.\n\nThe Kaifan, an oil products tanker owned by Kuwait Oil Tanker Co., was the vessel attacked in the strait, according to security consultancy EOS Risk Group. The ship was struck by an unknown projectile northeast of Oman’s Limah, UK Maritime Trade Operations said earlier Tuesday, without naming the tanker.\n#oott\nhttps://t.co/I5zmM3RS7W",
